    "causal_summary": "Five-iteration SOL xhigh-fast deep-research lineage on modeling the zero-signal branch as a calibrated one-turn negotiation: always expose rankScore and scoreMargin, expose estimatedError only when a versioned held-out corpus validates calibration, frame the whole thing as selective classification (auto-route under a validated risk budget, else one typed clarification, else defer/reject), and enforce a measurable friction budget (one turn, at most three candidates plus none_of_these, at most two attempts, a 256-token card) whose thresholds are promotable only from held-out risk/coverage",
